snippet.textDisplay: Wow I'm amazed by the level of detail in the artwork. At 1:00, that lady is painting Bhulan - the Indus river dolphin - on the wall which is a freshwater dolphin species pretty much native to Sindh now. Fun fact: These dolphins are nearly blind so they use echolocation to 'see' just like bats but their big elongated jaws work as sonar receivers. And they are super intelligent too.
